          <head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-573-D237-headnote-3">
            <lg n="1" xml:id="spp-573-D237-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote">
              <l n="1" xml:id="spp-573-D237-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l>
            </lg>
          </head>
          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-1" n="1"><hi rend="display-initial">W</hi>HEN our Gallants are preparing</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-2" n="2">In Vacation for an Airing,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-3" n="3">When Pease and Beans are ripe in Cods</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-4" n="4">And fit to shell from Heaps of Pods,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-5" n="5">And Cucumbers so very plenty</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-6" n="6">You may for Two pence purchase Twenty;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-7" n="7">When Gooseberries are ripe and full</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-8" n="8">And Currans are just fit to pull,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-9" n="9">Then the Active young A────s</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-10" n="10">Briskly Travel on their Journies,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-11" n="11">Some go off without delay</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-12" n="12">And <hi rend="italics">Sunday</hi> think the better Day</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-13" n="13">Because <hi rend="italics">Nem. Con</hi>. it is agreed</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-14" n="14"><hi rend="italics">The better Day, the better Deed</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-15" n="15">For sundry Reasons they could tell;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-16" n="16">To bid their Duns and Friends farewell.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-17" n="17">Then set out with borrowed Geer</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-18" n="18">For their Circuits far and near</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-19" n="19">Looking big as any Giants</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-20" n="20">On the Horses of their Clients</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-21" n="21">Like so many little Mars's</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-22" n="22">With their Tilters at their Arses</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-23" n="23">Brazen Tilters lately burnish'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-24" n="24">And with Harness Buckles furnish'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-25" n="25">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-26" n="26">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-27" n="27">And with Boots so very Greasy</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-28" n="28">And with Saddles Eke so easy</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-29" n="29">Saddles borrowed for a Day,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-30" n="30">Kept for ever and for Ay.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-31" n="31">Saddles destin'd far to Roam</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-32" n="32">Ah never to return Home.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-33" n="33">Hats with Gold or Silver Brac'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-34" n="34">Tho' by Duns and Bailiffs chac'd.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-35" n="35">And Valleeces fine and gay</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-36" n="36">Stuff'd, instead of Shirts, with Hay,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-37" n="37">Some accoutred like Knight Errants</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-38" n="38">Quit the Town for fear of Warrants,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-39" n="39">Some to Cork and some to Kerry,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-40" n="40">Others down to Londonderry.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-41" n="41">Where they feed on Meal and Whisky</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-42" n="42">And get Drunk with <hi rend="italics">Irish</hi> Isque.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-43" n="43">Another mounts a <hi rend="italics">Quadrupede</hi></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-44" n="44">Which sometimes he's forc'd to lead.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-45" n="45">Let him Walk or let him ride,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-46" n="46">Charg'd with Thirteen pence a Side.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-47" n="47">From the Hedges as he goes,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-48" n="48">Picks off Blackberries and Sloes</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-49" n="49">While <hi rend="italics">Garron</hi> feeds upon the Road,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-50" n="50">He lyes down to take a Nod.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-51" n="51">Empty Guts and Pockets bare,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-52" n="52">Highway-men he does not fear.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-53" n="53">In some Towns he is Caress'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-54" n="54">Thinks himself for ever bless'd.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-55" n="55">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-56" n="56">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-57" n="57">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-58" n="58">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-59" n="59">There he toys with Farmers Spouses,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-60" n="60">And makes Merry in their Houses.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-61" n="61">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-62" n="62">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-63" n="63">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-64" n="64">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-65" n="65">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-66" n="66">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-67" n="67">Those who have no far'd so well,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-68" n="68">Disappointments never tell:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-69" n="69">Tho' they lye upon the Ground,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-70" n="70">Where Straw nor Rushes can be found.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-71" n="71">Wish Vacation over, then</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-573-D237-line-72" n="72">Hey for <hi rend="italics">Dublin</hi> Town again.</l>
          </lg>
